history.content: In theory that is correct - grad students can enroll into the UG classes if you don't need the class to count for your requisites. However, when it comes to CS 189, your chances of getting in are EXTREMELY low given how impacted the class is and the fact that you do not have any priority access to seats.This class will not expand past room capacity.
As an aside to the instructor answer, i don't think CS189 in the fall will fill up due to instructor difference
To counter the instructor answer, i don't think CS189 in the fall will fill up due to instructor difference

children.subject: Well, in comparison at this time 189 from this semester was at 60% seats. Just checking Berkeleytime, every semester before this one ended below capacity after people dropped. It is unlikely, yes, but not naive to think that one could get into this class.

It's naive to think this class will not fill up no matter who is teaching it. Remember, this is a combination class and demand is high from a number of sources.

Enrollment has been opened less than a week and already appx 30% of seats are full. If you want to get into this class, postpone enrollment at your own risk.
